{"type":"message","id":"c72aa01f","parentId":"bfa48b25","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:23:09.924Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nq4mk4u81kli_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"========================================\n🔥 验证10: 深度安全审计\n========================================\nOpenClaw security audit\nSummary: 3 critical · 6 warn · 1 info\nRun deeper: openclaw security audit --deep\n\nCRITICAL\ngateway.loopback_no_auth Gateway auth missing on loopback\n  gateway.bind is loopback but no gateway auth secret is configured. If the Control UI is exposed through a reverse proxy, unauthenticated access is possible.\n  Fix: Set gateway.auth (token recommended) or keep the Control UI local-only.\nplugins.code_safety Plugin \"coze-openclaw-plugin\" contains dangerous code patterns\n  Found 2 critical issue(s) in 26 scanned file(s):\n  - [dangerous-exec] Shell command execution detected (child_process) (src/session-recovery.ts:311)\n  - [dangerous-exec] Shell command execution detected (child_process) (src/upgrade/applies-to.ts:61)\n  Fix: Review the plugin source code carefully before use. If untrusted, remove the plugin from your OpenClaw extensions state directory.\nplugins.code_safety Plugin \"wecom-openclaw-plugin\" contains dangerous code patterns\n  Found 2 critical issue(s) in 25 scanned file(s):\n  - [env-harvesting] Environment variable access combined with network send — possible credential harvesting (dist/index.esm.js:299)\n  - [env-harvesting] Environment variable access combined with network send — possible credential harvesting (dist/index.cjs.js:325)\n  Fix: Review the plugin source code carefully before use. If untrusted, remove the plugin from your OpenClaw extensions state directory.\n\nWARN\ngateway.trusted_proxies_missing Reverse proxy headers are not trusted\n  gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, configure trusted proxies so local-client checks cannot be spoofed.\n  Fix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.\nplugins.extensions_no_allowlist Extensions exist but plugins.allow is not set\n  Found 6 extension(s) under /workspace/projects/extensions. Without plugins.allow, any discovered plugin id may load (depending on config and plugin behavior).\n  Fix: Set plugins.allow to an explicit list of plugin ids you trust.\nplugins.tools_reachable_permissive_policy Extension plugin tools may be reachable under permissive tool policy\n  Enabled extension plugins: .openclaw-install-backups, coze-openclaw-plugin, openclaw-cozeloop-trace, openclaw-lark, openclaw-weixin, wecom-openclaw-plugin.\nPermissive tool policy contexts:\n- default\n  Fix: Use restrictive profiles (`minimal`/`coding`) or explicit tool allowlists that exclude plugin tools for agents handling untrusted input.\nplugins.code_safety Plugin \"openclaw-lark\" contains suspicious code patterns\n  Found 2 warning(s) in 379 scanned file(s):\n  - [potential-exfiltration] File read combined with network send — possible data exfiltration (src/tools/mcp/shared.js:94)\n  - [potential-exfiltration] File read combined with network send — possible data exfiltration (src/messaging/outbound/media.js:129)\n  Fix: Review the flagged code to ensure it is intentional and safe.\nplugins.code_safety Plugin \"openclaw-weixin\" contains suspicious code patterns\n  Found 2 warning(s) in 35 scanned file(s):\n  - [potential-exfiltration] File read combined with network send — possible data exfiltration (src/cdn/upload.ts:62)\n  - [potential-exfiltration] File read combined with network send — possible data exfiltration (src/api/api.ts:43)\n  Fix: Review the flagged code to ensure it is intentional and safe.\ngateway.probe_failed Gateway probe failed (deep)\n  device identity required\n  Fix: Run \"openclaw status --all\" to debug connectivity/auth, then re-run \"openclaw security audit --deep\".\n\nINFO\nsummary.attack_surf